@startuml likePost
!include ../../theme/theme-dark-seq.puml
title likePost flow
actor User
participant Resolver
participant PostsService as P
participant LikesService as L
participant ActivityService as A
database DB

User -> Resolver: likePost()
Resolver -> P: likePost() : bool

group postsRepo.manager.transaction
  P -> DB: manager.findOne(User)
  DB --> P: user

  P -> DB: lockEntityByIdOrThrow(Post) + load user relation
  DB --> P: post

  P -> L: like()
  L -> DB: repo.findOne()
  DB --> L: like | null

  note over L,P
  Overall flow:
  - if like is already active, return success immediately
  - otherwise activate or create the like
  - then log post-like activity
  end note

  alt existing like is active
    L --> P: changed = false
    P -> P: skip activity log (idempotent)
  else like state changed
    alt existing inactive like
      L -> DB: repo.save() [active=false -> true]
      DB --> L: like reactivated
    else no existing like
      L -> DB: repo.save()
      DB --> L: like saved
    end
    L --> P: changed = true

    P -> A: logActivity()
    A -> DB: repo.query()
    DB --> A: activity row
    A --> P: activity
  end
end

P --> Resolver: true
Resolver --> User: data.likePost = true

== Error rule ==
note over P,DB
If any awaited step inside the transaction throws:
TypeORM issues ROLLBACK, then error bubbles to resolver,
and resolver returns a GraphQL error.
end note
@enduml
